\pard\nowidctlpar\b0\par
\pard This is a beta release version 0.7.3 of Component Synthesis using Model-Integrated Computing ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.dre.vanderbilt.edu/cosmic" }}{\fldrslt{\cf1\ul CoSMIC}}}\cf0\ulnone\f0\fs20 ) suite of tools. Currently CoSMIC tool suite consists of Platform-Independent Component Modeling Language (PICML), Component QoS Modeling Language (CQML), DDS QoS Modeling Language (DQML). \par
\par
PICML is a Model-Integrated Computing ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.isis.vanderbilt.edu/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf1\ul MIC}}}\cf0\ulnone\f0\fs20 ) based paradigm for modeling CORBA Component Model ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.omg.org/technology/documents/formal/components.htm" }}{\fldrslt{\cf1\ul CCM}}}\cf0\ulnone\f0\fs20 ) based applications, which use the latest Deployment and Configuration Specification {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.omg.org/cgi-bin/doc?ptc/2003-07-02" }}{\fldrslt{\cf1\ul (D&C)}}}\cf0\ulnone\f0\fs20 , for configuration and deployment. CQML allows PICML-based models to capture the higher level QoS design intent and helps generate QoS configuration metadata from annotated models. DQML allows modeling of large number QoS knobs provided by DDS.\par
\par
This document lists the new features that are introduced in the latest version.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\par
\ul\b Release CoSMIC-0.7.3\par
