\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720\tx720\f1\'b7\tab\f0 PICML:\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li1440\tx1440\f2 o\tab\f0 Enabled support for modeling complex type Property elements, such as collections, aggregates, and enums.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720\tx720\f1\'b7\tab\f0 PICMLManager: \par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li1440\tx1440\f2 o\tab\f0 It replaces old UUIDManager addon. \par
\pard\fi-360\li1440\qj\tx1440\f2 o\tab\f0 Handles generating a unique name for the PublishConnector object when its added to a component assembly.\par
\pard\fi-360\li1440\qj\f2 o\tab\f0 When an AttributeValue connection is added to a model, i.e., creating a connection between an attribute and a property, the manager ensures the referenced data type in the property is the correct type. This includes autonomously adding the correct data type to the property, or making sure the current referenced data type is the same type as the attribute.\par
\f2 o\tab\f0 When an attribute is given a new data type, PICMLManager ensures that all properties of the target attribute in the component assembly model has the newly selected data type.\par
\f2 o\tab\f0 When an ExternalDelegate connection is created between an ExternalPortReference and a port (e.g., ProvidedEventPort, RequiredEventPort, InEventPort, or OutEventPort), the referenced object for the ExternalEventPort is set to the referenced object for the target port.\par
\pard\fi-360\li1440\tx1440\f2 o\tab\f0 Contact: James H. Hill  <hillj@isis.vanderbilt.edu>\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\tx720\f1\'b7\tab\f0 PropertyManager:\par
\pard\fi-360\li1440\tx1440\f2 o\tab\f0 A new interpreter that simplifies setting the values of complex type Property values.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720\tx720\f1\'b7\tab\f0 Component Behavior Modeling Language (CBML) has new features.\par
\pard\fi-360\li1440\tx1440\f2 o\tab\f0 Added modeling support for do-while, for, and while loops. They have the same modeling semantics as branch states.\par
\f2 o\tab\f0 Contact: James H. Hill  <hillj@isis.vanderbilt.edu>\par
