\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720\qj\tx720\f1\'b7\tab\f0 A new paradigm called CQML captures higher level system quality-of-service (QoS) design intent of the designer. Following is a list of different QoS modeling capabilities of CQML:\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li1440\qj\tx1440\f2 o\tab\f0 Fault-tolerance aspect modeling supports modeling of protected components, degree of replication, replication style and more. The interpreter augments deployment plan with replica components, connections and decides a placement for all the components.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li1440\qj\f2 o\tab\f0 Network QoS modeling supports modeling of bidirectional bandwidth requirements of CCM level connections. Also it supports traffic characteristic modeling.\par
\f2 o\tab\f0 Real-time configuration model checking capabilities using BOGOR generates the Bogor Input Representation (BIR) for RT configuration options (component-level) specified in CQML models.\par
\f2 o\tab\f0 Real-time configuration modeling supports modeling of Real-time options at the component level. The interpreter generates correspondingly server resources file(s) and augments the deployment plan with RT policies for that plan.\par
\f2 o\tab\f0 Security QoS modeling allows the modeling of Security QoS policies and Role-Based Access Control to allow specification of permissions on resource access such as assemblies, components, ports, operations, attributes, critical paths, etc.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\li1440\qj\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\li360\qj\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720\qj\tx720\f1\'b7\tab\f0 DeploymentPlanFramework (DPFramework) is an extensible framework that provides a fixed set of extension points where a deployment plan can be extended with QoS specific metadata. Many of the CQML interpreters are implemented as extensions to the DPFramework.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\qj\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\par
